    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Fix the Error\r\n\r\nThe <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">findMatchingMeal()</code> method in the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Menu</code> class is supposed to return a <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">String</code> containing the text <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">\"All of the options are the same!\"</code> if all <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">MenuItem</code> objects in the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Menu</code> are the same, but it has a bug 🪲\r\n\r\nFind and fix the error in the program.\r\n\r\n<details style=\"background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;\">\r\n    <summary style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-weight: bold;\">🔦 Help! I can't find the bug!</summary>\r\n    <div style=\"margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;\">\r\n    \t<p>The <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">equals()</code> method in the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">MenuItem</code> class returns <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">true</code> if two <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">MenuItem</code> objects have the same type. Check if this is being used in the condition in the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">findMatchingMeal()</code> method.</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n</details>\r\n",
